title: february 17: the new yorker
description:
Today on 365 days with mxmtoon, Maia talks about the first ever print issue of the New Yorker, the magazine known for its dry humor, political commentary and prose. Turning to music, she talks about the Bob Dylan and Johnny Cash album that was never released.
